            I liked Messi's second goal so much. Classic Messi. Jordi Alba was a superstar and Sergi Roberto was tremendous. Barca is crazy lucky that they have Umtiti. He reads the game so well. I'm surprised Turan wasn't involved more after his CL performance during the week. I'm also surprised Osasuna didn't find a goal. They looked like they might in the first half. The referee had an...interesting game. Ahem. I think he didn't call a few fouls in Osasuna's favor, but then he also let a lot of things go with how physical Osasuna was willing to be with Barca. Iniesta's defensive contribution is underrated. And Messi is Messi. It's impossible to define him. It seems the more difficult the goal, the more likely he is to score. Crazy angles or five defenders in the way? No problem, certain goal. One on one with the keeper? Keeper saves (kidding! Messi is a miracle). During the second half, Barca played more like Barca. What does Enrique say to them in the locker room?
